Incremental aggregators are aggregate functions for which computations are possible only by using previous aggregate value and the new value. For example,  SUM = {Previous_SUM} + {Current_Value}
COUNT = {Previous_COUNT}  + 1
MIN = ( {Current_Value}   {Previous_MIN} ) ? {Current_Value} : {Previous_MIN}

